"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449286","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-17","Until 31 March 2014, HM Revenue and Customs’ (HMRC) Large Business Service dealt with the tax affairs of around 800 of the largest businesses in the UK. From 1 April 2014, HMRC’s new Large Business directorate deals with the tax affairs of around 2,000 large businesses.<p> </p>At 31 December 2015, HMRC had enquiries open with 1,117 of the large businesses dealt with by the Large Business Directorate, covering 3,981 risks with £20.3 billion tax under consideration.<p> </p>At 31 December 2015, HMRC had enquiries open with 567 of the largest 800 businesses covering 2,826 risks with £16.8 billion tax under consideration.<p> </p><p>Tax under consideration is not actual tax either owed or unpaid. Rather, it is a tool which HMRC uses to guide its enquiries to focus on the most significant risks that exist at any particular time. The total is just a snapshot of work in progress and will naturally fluctuate as risks are addressed and new ones taken up.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449286/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-17T10:03:13.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449286/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449286/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-01","Business: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many tax disputes with large businesses HM Revenue and Customs is engaged in; and what the value is of the tax that is being contested in those disputes.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","25102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449287","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-09","<p>The information is not held in the form requested. The estimated amounts of Patent Box relief can be found at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/487119/Dec15_expenditure_reliefs_Final.xlsx.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/487119/Dec15_expenditure_reliefs_Final.xlsx.pdf</a></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449287/answer",,,,,"25092 ; 25093 ; 25094 ; 25095","2016-02-09T17:00:50.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449287/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449287/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-01","Patents: Corporation Tax","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many companies have paid a lower rate of corporation tax as a result of the patent box initiative since its implementation.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","25091"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449288","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-09","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) does not publish this information. Since 2010, HMRC has brought in over £38 billion by effectively policing the tax rules as they apply to large businesses. This includes £7.3 billion from large businesses in 2014/15 alone.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449288/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-09T15:27:51.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449288/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449288/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-01","Business: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many tax investigations by the HM Revenue and Customs Large Business Service resulted in no additional tax due at the time of their conclusion in each of the last three years; and for how long each such investigation lasted.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","25254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449289","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-09","<p>The Government received a large number of responses to the business rates review. The review will be fiscally neutral and will report at Budget 2016.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449289/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-09T17:09:10.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449289/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449289/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-02-01","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what progress  he is making on his Department's review of business rates; and when he plans to report the findings of that review to the House.","false","Biography information for Mrs Anne Main","St Albans","Mrs Anne Main","25232"
