 Repair work on individual ship systems takes place during both planned maintenance periods and operational deployments and data relating to the number of days’ worth of repair work is not collected. Unprogrammed work/repair figures shown cover the extension of maintenance periods.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Name of Ship</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>In-Service Date</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Maintenance/</strong> <strong>Repair </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Duration</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DARING</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>July 2010</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>360</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p>105</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DAUNTLESS</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>November 2010</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>215</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p>20</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DIAMOND</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>July 2011</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>350</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DRAGON</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>April 2012</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>250</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DEFENDER</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>March 2013</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>HMS DUNCAN</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p>December 2013</p></td><td><p>Programmed Maintenance</p></td><td><p>130</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Unprogrammed Work/Repair</p></td><td><p><strong>0</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449332/an