"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449498","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-05","<p>Information published by my Department on 22 June 2015 shows that, during the original Troubled Families Programme (2012 to 2015), 104,733 were turned around through achieving reductions in youth crime, and/or anti-social behaviour, combined with satisfactory levels of school attendance.</p><p>Under the provisions of the Welfare Reform and Work Bill, I will be reporting annually on the progress and impact of the new Troubled Families Programme which aims to reach up to an additional 400,000 families.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449498/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-05T13:16:06.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449498/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449498/answer","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449498/answer/previousversion/43466","Biography information for Greg Clark","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-02-01","Reoffenders: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the success rates of the troubled families programme in reducing re-offending among young adults.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","25064"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449499","Ministry of Justice","false","2016-02-04","<p>The information requested is not held.</p><p> </p><p>Jury service is an important civic duty. HMCTS is committed to offering support to those called as jurors. Financial provision is made for jurors who are on benefit and for those who suffer loss of earning whilst on jury service. Full details of that provision can be found at: www.gov.uk/jury-service/what-you-can-claim</p><p> </p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449499/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-04T15:18:36.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449499/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/449499/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2016-02-01","Juries: Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people called for Jury service were in receipt of (a) jobseeker's allowance, (b) employment and support allowance, (c) income support, (d) working tax credit and (e) child tax credit in the most recent 12 months for which data is available; and what steps he is taking to meet the costs of undertaking jury service for such people.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","25056"
