"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448955","HM Treasury","false","2016-02-03","<p>HM Treasury has received representations on applying a five per cent rate of VAT to golf from both the Association of Golf Course Owners, the Reduce VAT in Sport campaign group, the UK Golf Course Owners Association, and England Golf.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448955/answer",,,,,,"2016-02-03T16:05:40.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448955/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/448955/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-01-29","Golf: VAT","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what representations his Department has received on allowing a five per cent rate of VAT to golf participants at proprietary golf facilities.","false","Biography information for Karl McCartney","Lincoln","Karl McCartney","24909"
